<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Write the following expression as a perfect square:</p>

<p>
<me>
{x^2-24 x+144}
</me>
</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
Compare the expression with:
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x + a)^2 = x^2 + 2ax + a^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
(x - a)^2 = x^2 - 2ax + a^2
</me>
</p>

<p>
The constant term is <m>{144}</m> = (<m>{12}</m>)^2,
so the number inside the bracket is <m>{12}</m>.
</p>

<p>
The middle term is <m>{-24}</m>x,
which matches <m>\pm 2ax</m>.
</p>

<p>
Therefore,
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{{{\left(x-12\right)}^2}}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>{\left(x-12\right)}^2</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>